-- Citigroup’s Corbat to Hold Call Today After Replacing Pandit
-- B y   S u s a n n a   P a k
-- 2012-10-16T19:16:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-16/citigroup-s-corbat-to-hold-call-today-after-replacing-pandit.html
Citigroup Inc., the third-largest
U.S. bank, said Chief Executive Officer Michael Corbat will host
a teleconference with analysts today after he was named to
replace Vikram Pandit as leader of the company.  Chairman  Michael O’Neill  will also participate in the
event, which is scheduled for 4:30 p.m. in New York, the lender
said today in a statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susanna Pak in New York at 
 Spak10@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Kraut at   dkraut2@bloomberg.net  